volved in several experiment based research studies with the goal of providing policymakers with clear scientific results that can help shape successful policies to improve the effectiveness of k 12 rural education programs and the educational experiences of young chinese rural students since 1998 she has worked on the gansu survey of children and families a longitudinal research project that investigates family school and community factors that support children's education and healthy development in rural northwest china she is also working on other research including an analysis of chinese educational policy trends and an investigation of the schools in sending and receiving communities for the children of migrant workers in addition to her experience as a researcher adams also has five years of experience teaching primary school in greater china stanford departments school of education publications behind before they begin the challenge of early childhood education in rural china renfu luo linxiu zhang chengfang liu scott rozelle brian sharbono jennifer adams australian journal of early childhood 2011 pdf+ early commitment on financial aid and college decision making of poor students evidence from randomized evaluation in rural china chengfang liu linxiu zhang renfu luo scott rozelle brian sharbono jennifer adams yaojiang shi ai yue hongbin li xiaobing wang thomas glauben economics of education review 2011 pdf+ choices hopes and expectations does gender still shape access to basic education in rural northwest china jennifer adams emily hannum maureen lewis marlaine lockheed in social exclusion gender and education case studies from the developing world maureen lewis ed and marlaine lockheed ed 2009 community matters in china jennifer adams emily hannum bruce fuller research in sociology of education 15 social organization of childhood in developing countries vol 15 2006 children's social welfare in china jennifer adams emily hannum access to health insurance and 